FBIS3-13704 "drnes053dd_94004" FBIS-NES-94-053 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Receives Letter From Russian Leadership LD1803093794 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0600 GMT 18 Mar 94 LD1803093794 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] President 'Arafat received another letter from the Russian leadership yesterday evening. The letter was handed to him by the Russian ambassador in Tunis, with whom he discussed the latest developments and the current consultations aimed at speeding up the adoption of the UN Security Council draft resolution which has been outstanding for over 19 days. This draft resolution calls for the condemnation of the Hebron massacre, the provision of international protection for the Palestinian people, the disarming of settlers, and the introduction of the necessary arrangements to protect the Palestinian people in the occupied territories, particularly in Hebron.
